  "steps": [
    "Split non-transduced, confluent cells 1:5 in 10 ml DMEM + 10% FBS media. 00:05:00",
    "Transfer 0.5 mL cell suspension into 24-well plate containing 500 µl of (media + drug). - G418 Sulfate - Hygromycin B - Puromycin Dihydrochloride 00:08:00",
    "Examine viability every 2 days. 48:00:00",
    "Culture for 14 days. Replace the media containing antibiotic every 3 days. 72:00:00",
    "Use the lowest concentration of your antibiotic that begins to give massive cell death in 3 days and kills all the cells within two weeks. A general starting point is usually 400 mg/ml G418 for HeLa cells and 200 mg/ml hygromycin for CHO cells. In mammalian cells the optimal level of puromycin is typically around 1 mg/ml. HeLa cells are often selectable with 500 mg/ml G418, 500 mg/ml hygromycin, or 2.5 mg/ml puromycin, and SHSY-5Y cells are often selectable with 600 mg/ml G418 or 200mg/ml hygromycin. Hygromycin B P212121 Catalog #GB-T005"
